; Print digits of 9274 on four lines using only DIV/MOD (unrolled).
; Strategy: at each step we have the remaining number N on the stack.
; We compute N / 10 -> quotient (kept), N % 10 -> next digit (printed).
; Print the digit we just extracted.
; For 9274:
;   9274 / 10 = 927  r 4
;   927  / 10 = 92   r 7
;   92   / 10 = 9    r 2
;   9    / 10 = 0    r 9  (we stop printing the leading 9 when N becomes 0... no,
;                            spec says "digits of 9274" so we WANT the 9 too)
; We unroll: just do the 4 passes (the last one will have N=9, /10=0, %10=9).
PUSH 9274
PUSH 10
MOD
PRINT
PUSH 9274
PUSH 10
DIV
PUSH 10
MOD
PRINT
PUSH 927
PUSH 10
DIV
PUSH 10
MOD
PRINT
PUSH 92
PUSH 10
DIV
PUSH 10
MOD
PRINT
HALT
